  <section class="section" id="about">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>Satish Kumar is a passionate science communicator who makes the cosmos accessible to all. His writing blends scientific rigor with philosophical wonder, inviting each reader to feel their connection to the stars.</p>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:kalivarapu.satish1@gmail.com">kalivarapu.satish1@gmail.com</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="book">
    <h2>My Book</h2>
    <p><strong>You Are the Cosmos: A Journey Through Space</strong></p>
    <p>This book takes you from the Big Bang to black holes, exploring the illusion of time, dark matter, alien life, and humanity's place in the universe. Each chapter mixes cutting-edge science with poetic perspective and meaning.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Big Bang & cosmic evolution</li>
      <li>Time and its mysteries</li>
      <li>Dark matter & dark energy</li>
      <li>Black holes, multiverse, alien life</li>
      <li>Consciousness & our cosmic role</li>
    </ul>
    <p><a href="https://amzn.in/d/iPWPQMT" target="_blank">Buy on Amazon (Kindle/Paperback)</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="excerpts">
    <h2>Excerpts</h2>
    <blockquote>
      "You are not just in the universe—you are the universe. This is not a metaphor, but a startling scientific truth hidden in plain sight."
    </blockquote>
    <blockquote>
      "The iron in your blood, the calcium in your bones, the oxygen you breathe—they were all forged in the hearts of massive stars that lived and died billions of years ago."
    </blockquote>
  </section>

